verses.text_plain: Doth not wisdom cry? and understanding put forth her voice?
verses.verse_html: 1Doth not wisdom cry? and understanding put forth her voice?

verses.text_plain: She standeth in the top of high places, by the way in the places of the paths.
verses.verse_html: 2She standeth in the top of high places, by the way in the places of the paths.

verses.text_plain: She crieth at the gates, at the entry of the city, at the coming in at the doors.
verses.verse_html: 3She crieth at the gates, at the entry of the city, at the coming in at the doors.

verses.text_plain: Unto you, O men, I call; and my voice is to the sons of man.
verses.verse_html: 4Unto you, O men, I call; and my voice is to the sons of man.

verses.text_plain: O ye simple, understand wisdom: and, ye fools, be ye of an understanding heart.
verses.verse_html: 5O ye simple, understand wisdom: and, ye fools, be ye of an understanding heart.

verses.text_plain: Hear; for I will speak of excellent things; and the opening of my lips shall be right things.
verses.verse_html: 6Hear; for I will speak of excellent things; and the opening of my lips shall be right things.

verses.text_plain: For my mouth shall speak truth; and wickedness is an abomination to my lips.
verses.verse_html:
7For my mouth shall speak truth; and wickedness is an abomination to my lips. ▼
▼ an…: Heb. the abomination of my lips

footnotes.body_text: ▼ an…: Heb. the abomination of my lips
footnotes.body_html: ▼ an…: Heb. the abomination of my lips

verses.text_plain: All the words of my mouth are in righteousness; there is nothing froward or perverse in them.
verses.verse_html:
8All the words of my mouth are in righteousness; there is nothing froward or perverse in them. ▼
▼ froward: Heb. wreathed

verses.text_plain: They are all plain to him that understandeth, and right to them that find knowledge.
verses.verse_html: 9They are all plain to him that understandeth, and right to them that find knowledge.

verses.text_plain: Receive my instruction, and not silver; and knowledge rather than choice gold.
verses.verse_html: 10Receive my instruction, and not silver; and knowledge rather than choice gold.

verses.text_plain: For wisdom is better than rubies; and all the things that may be desired are not to be compared to it.
verses.verse_html: 11For wisdom is better than rubies; and all the things that may be desired are not to be compared to it.

tokens.text: and all the things that may be desired

verses.text_plain: I wisdom dwell with prudence, and find out knowledge of witty inventions.
verses.verse_html:
12I wisdom dwell with prudence, and find out knowledge of witty inventions. ▼
▼ prudence: or, subtilty

verses.text_plain: The fear of the Lord is to hate evil: pride, and arrogancy, and the evil way, and the froward mouth, do I hate.
verses.verse_html: 13The fear of the Lord is to hate evil: pride, and arrogancy, and the evil way, and the froward mouth, do I hate.

verses.text_plain: Counsel is mine, and sound wisdom: I am understanding; I have strength.
verses.verse_html: 14Counsel is mine, and sound wisdom: I am understanding; I have strength.

verses.text_plain: By me kings reign, and princes decree justice.
verses.verse_html: 15By me kings reign, and princes decree justice.

verses.text_plain: By me princes rule, and nobles, even all the judges of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 16By me princes rule, and nobles, even all the judges of the earth.

verses.text_plain: I love them that love me; and those that seek me early shall find me.
verses.verse_html: 17I love them that love me; and those that seek me early shall find me.

tokens.text: me; and those that seek me early

verses.text_plain: Riches and honour are with me; yea, durable riches and righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 18Riches and honour are with me; yea, durable riches and righteousness.

verses.text_plain: My fruit is better than gold, yea, than fine gold; and my revenue than choice silver.
verses.verse_html: 19My fruit is better than gold, yea, than fine gold; and my revenue than choice silver.

verses.text_plain: I lead in the way of righteousness, in the midst of the paths of judgment:
verses.verse_html:
20I lead in the way of righteousness, in the midst of the paths of judgment: ▼
▼ lead: or, walk

verses.text_plain: That I may cause those that love me to inherit substance; and I will fill their treasures.
verses.verse_html: 21That I may cause those that love me to inherit substance; and I will fill their treasures.

tokens.text: That I may cause those that love

verses.text_plain: The Lord possessed me in the beginning of his way, before his works of old.
verses.verse_html: 22The Lord possessed me in the beginning of his way, before his works of old.

verses.text_plain: I was set up from everlasting, from the beginning, or ever the earth was.
verses.verse_html: 23I was set up from everlasting, from the beginning, or ever the earth was.

verses.text_plain: When there were no depths, I was brought forth; when there were no fountains abounding with water.
verses.verse_html: 24When there were no depths, I was brought forth; when there were no fountains abounding with water.

verses.text_plain: Before the mountains were settled, before the hills was I brought forth:
verses.verse_html: 25Before the mountains were settled, before the hills was I brought forth:

verses.text_plain: While as yet he had not made the earth, nor the fields, nor the highest part of the dust of the world.
verses.verse_html:
26While as yet he had not made the earth, nor the fields, nor the highest part of the dust of the world. ▼
▼ fields: or, open places
 , ▼
▼ the highest…: or, the chief part

tokens.text: While as yet he had not made

footnotes.body_html: ▼ fields: or, open places

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the highest…: or, the chief part
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the highest…: or, the chief part

verses.text_plain: When he prepared the heavens, I was there: when he set a compass upon the face of the depth:
verses.verse_html:
27When he prepared the heavens, I was there: when he set a compass upon the face of the depth: ▼
▼ a compass: or, a circle

footnotes.body_html: ▼ a compass: or, a circle

verses.text_plain: When he established the clouds above: when he strengthened the fountains of the deep:
verses.verse_html: 28When he established the clouds above: when he strengthened the fountains of the deep:

verses.text_plain: When he gave to the sea his decree, that the waters should not pass his commandment: when he appointed the foundations of the earth:
verses.verse_html: 29When he gave to the sea his decree, that the waters should not pass his commandment: when he appointed the foundations of the earth:

verses.text_plain: Then I was by him, as one brought up with him: and I was daily his delight, rejoicing always before him;
verses.verse_html: 30Then I was by him, as one brought up with him: and I was daily his delight, rejoicing always before him;

verses.text_plain: Rejoicing in the habitable part of his earth; and my delights were with the sons of men.
verses.verse_html: 31Rejoicing in the habitable part of his earth; and my delights were with the sons of men.

verses.text_plain: Now therefore hearken unto me, O ye children: for blessed are they that keep my ways.
verses.verse_html: 32Now therefore hearken unto me, O ye children: for blessed are they that keep my ways.

verses.text_plain: Hear instruction, and be wise, and refuse it not.
verses.verse_html: 33Hear instruction, and be wise, and refuse it not.

verses.text_plain: Blessed is the man that heareth me, watching daily at my gates, waiting at the posts of my doors.
verses.verse_html: 34Blessed is the man that heareth me, watching daily at my gates, waiting at the posts of my doors.

verses.text_plain: For whoso findeth me findeth life, and shall obtain favour of the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
35For whoso findeth me findeth life, and shall obtain favour of the Lord. ▼
▼ obtain: Heb. bring forth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ obtain: Heb. bring forth

verses.text_plain: But he that sinneth against me wrongeth his own soul: all they that hate me love death.
verses.verse_html: 36But he that sinneth against me wrongeth his own soul: all they that hate me love death.
